14 Section 3. Section 90-4-607, MCA, is amended to read:
15 "90-4-607. Duties of department division. In addition to the duties set forth in 90-4-605, the
16 department division is authorized to:
17 (1) analyze state utility data to identify high-potential energy conservation projects;
18 (2) perform comprehensive energy analyses on state-owned buildings, structures, and facilities,
19 contracting with private engineers when necessary;
20 (3) transfer funds and authority to the department of administration to:
21 (a)(3) procure design and construction of cost-effective energy improvements; and
22 (b)(4) transfer funds and authority to other agencies to procure, design, and construct cost-effective
23 energy improvements; and
24 (4)(5) train facility maintenance staff in energy saving techniques and maintenance of energy
25 improvements and monitor energy conservation projects to ensure that cost savings are realized and are
26 adequate to cover the debt service if bonds have been issued to fund the improvements."
